                <h1>Understanding Galatians: Faith Over Law</h1>
                <p>Galatians is a letter in the New Testament attributed to the Apostle Paul. It addresses the early Christian communities in Galatia, emphasizing salvation through faith in Christ apart from the Law. Paul defends his apostolic authority and stresses the importance of living by the Spirit, guiding believers in their faith journey towards freedom in Christ.</p>
